<TITLE> Japan foreign minister admitted to hospital -Kyodo </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 TOKYO, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Japan's foreign minister, Masahiro Komura, has been hospitalised after complaining he felt ill, but he is not in a serious condition, Kyodo news agency said on Saturday, quoting a government source. Komura, 65, became sick during a dinner meeting on Friday night with Slovakian Foreign Minister Jan Kubis and was showing symptoms of anaemia, Kyodo reported. Komura, appointed to the cabinet by new Prime Minister Yasuo Fukuda last month, underwent surgery just over a year ago for acute inflammation of the gall bladder. The previous prime minister, Shinzo Abe, has been in hospital since he stepped down last month
